        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix agents-providers-missing-external",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- keep `agents list` provider entries visible when a binding points at a configured external channel plugin that is not installed in the current runtime\r\n- avoid dropping the route/provider row just because runtime registry normalization is unavailable for that channel id\r\n- add focused regression coverage for both provider listing and routing summary output\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/agents.providers.test.ts`\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/agents.commands.list.test.ts`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- `Behavior addressed:` `openclaw agents list` now keeps the configured provider row for an uninstalled official external channel plugin and shows the repair hint instead of silently omitting it.\r\n- `Real environment tested:` packaged OpenClaw `2026.6.8` tarball installed with `npm install /Users/shen/Documents/GitHub/openclaw/openclaw-2026.6.8.tgz` in a fresh temp project on macOS.\r\n- `Exact steps or command run after this patch:` created `.openclaw/openclaw.json` with a `feishu` binding and ran `HOME=\"$PWD\" npx openclaw agents list`.\r\n- \r\n- `Evidence after fix:` output included:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n```text\r\nRouting: Feishu default\r\nProviders:\r\n  - Feishu default: missing plugin - Install the official external plugin with: openclaw plugins install @openclaw/feishu, or run: openclaw doctor --fix.\r\n\r\nshen@shendeMac-mini openclaw-pr-95266-proof % npm install /Users/shen/Documents/GitHub/openclaw/openclaw-*.tgz\r\nnpm warn EBADENGINE Unsupported engine {\r\nnpm warn EBADENGINE   package: 'hosted-git-info@10.1.1',\r\nnpm warn EBADENGINE   required: { node: '^22.22.2 || ^24.15.0 || >=26.0.0' },\r\nnpm warn EBADENGINE   current: { node: 'v22.22.0', npm: '10.9.4' }\r\nnpm warn EBADENGINE }\r\nnpm warn deprecated node-domexception@1.0.0: Use your platform's native DOMException instead\r\n\r\nadded 298 packages in 20s\r\n\r\n67 packages are looking for funding\r\n  run `npm fund` for details\r\nshen@shendeMac-mini openclaw-pr-95266-proof % mkdir -p .openclaw\r\nshen@shendeMac-mini openclaw-pr-95266-proof % cat > .openclaw/openclaw.json <<'EOF'\r\n{\r\n  \"gateway\": { \"mode\": \"local\" },\r\n  \"agents\": { \"list\": [{ \"id\": \"main\", \"default\": true }] },\r\n  \"bindings\": [{ \"agentId\": \"main\", \"match\": { \"channel\": \"feishu\" } }],\r\n  \"channels\": { \"feishu\": { \"appId\": \"cli_xxx\" } }\r\n}\r\nEOF\r\nshen@shendeMac-mini openclaw-pr-95266-proof % HOME=\"$PWD\" npx openclaw agents list\r\n\r\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.6.8 (fbcee43)\r\n   More integrations than your therapist's intake form.\r\n\r\nAgents:\r\n- main (default)\r\n  Workspace: ~/.openclaw/workspace\r\n  Agent dir: ~/.openclaw/agents/main/agent\r\n  Routing rules: 1\r\n  Routing: Feishu default\r\n  Providers:\r\n    - Feishu default: missing plugin - Install the official external plugin with: openclaw plugins install @openclaw/feishu, or run: openclaw doctor --fix.\r\nRouting rules map channel/account/peer to an agent. Use --bindings for full rules.\r\nChannel status reflects local config/creds. For live health: openclaw channels status --probe.\r\nnpm notice\r\nnpm notice New major version of npm available! 10.9.4 -> 11.17.0\r\nnpm notice Changelog: https://github.com/npm/cli/releases/tag/v11.17.0\r\nnpm notice To update run: npm install -g npm@11.17.0\r\nnpm notice\r\n```\r\n\r\n- `Observed result after fix:` the CLI preserved the configured provider entry and surfaced the missing-plugin recovery guidance in packaged runtime output.\r\n- `What was not tested:` no live Feishu login or message send path was exercised; this proof covers packaged CLI rendering for the missing-plugin configuration state.\r\n",
